# Cloudflare Pages security headers.
# Served for every path. No build step or dependency involved.
#
# The strict CSP is possible because this site executes NO JavaScript and loads
# NO external resources — every asset is self-hosted. Keep it that way: adding
# analytics, embeds, or CDN fonts would force this policy to be weakened.
#
# Notes:
# - default-src 'none' blocks scripts entirely (we run none). The JSON-LD blocks
#   are <script type="application/ld+json">, which are data blocks, not executed
#   script — they are unaffected and remain readable to crawlers.
# - style-src needs 'unsafe-inline' because Astro inlines one scoped <style> per
#   page. With no JavaScript and no user-supplied content there is no realistic
#   injection vector, so CSP hashes are not worth the build complexity.
# - frame-ancestors 'none' supersedes X-Frame-Options.
# - HSTS intentionally omits `preload` — that is a hard-to-reverse commitment.

/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'none'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self'; font-src 'self'; base-uri 'none'; form-action 'none'; frame-ancestors 'none'; upgrade-insecure-requests
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains
  Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(), camera=(), microphone=(), payment=(), usb=()
  Referrer-Policy: same-origin
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
